                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/6262a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="9" xml:id="d637fn9">The same on the same date to the
                        Minister in Honduras as telegram No. 31.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-04-13T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 13, 1929—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>53. Press reports that a conference is being held on the frontier between high
                    officials of the Honduran Government and American Marine officers for the
                    purpose of agreeing on measures to prevent “further invasions of Honduran
                    territory”. Please keep the Department fully informed about this matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
